Round 1:
[Patient] "What foods can I eat to help with my heart failure?"
[Educator] "Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins like fish or chicken."

Round 2:
[Patient] "Are there any specific foods I should avoid?"
[Educator] "Limit salt, processed foods, sugary drinks, and high-fat foods like fried items."

Round 3:
[Patient] "I love soul food, can I still eat it?"
[Educator] "Yes, you can enjoy soul food but opt for healthier cooking methods like grilling or baking."

Round 4:
[Patient] "What about fast food, can I have it sometimes?"
[Educator] "Occasional fast food is okay, but try to make healthier choices like salads or grilled options."

Round 5:
